{# Custom release-notes template.

   Why this exists: PSR's bundled `.components/changes.md.j2` (still v10.5.3)
   indexes `breaking_descriptions.0` inside a `selectattr`, which raises
   "list object has no element 0" any time a release contains a commit with
   no breaking descriptions (i.e. almost every release). PSR prefers this
   file over the bundled one when it lives in `template_dir`, so we sidestep
   the bug by owning the template.
#}
## {{ release.version.as_tag() }} ({{ release.tagged_date.strftime("%Y-%m-%d") }})
{% for type_, commits in release["elements"] | dictsort %}
{% if commits | length > 0 %}

### {{ type_ | title }}
{% for commit in commits %}
- {{ commit.commit.summary.rstrip() }} ([`{{ commit.commit.hexsha[:7] }}`]({{ commit.commit.hexsha | commit_hash_url }}))
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}
{% endfor %}
